\;\large \frac{2x}{1+x^{2}}\;?\;
\,(1+x^2)\,
u = 1 + x^2,\;
du = 2x \,dx.\; 
2x=(1+x^2)'
\int{\frac{(1+x^2)'}{(1+x^2)}}dx
\textbf{Hint:}
\displaystyle \int \frac{2x}{1+x^2}dx=\int \frac{(1+x^2)'}{1+x^2}dx=\log {\bigl(|1+x^2|\bigr)}=\log {(1+x^2)}
\displaystyle\frac{\mathrm{d}}{\mathrm{d}x} \ln u(x) =\frac{u'(x)}{u(x)} 
u(x)=x^2+1
\ln(x^2+1)+C
